supportDesc.support:
                           Written on good-quality membrane; in vols. III and IV especially, many entire bottom and even side margins from which strips (no doubt usable) had been excised were entirely replaced, probably at the time of the rebinding in s. xviii.

Fore- and endleaves: (I) fols. irv, Irv, blank; (II) fols. fols. irv, Irv, blank; 
                              (III) fols. ir-iiv, Irv, blank; (IV) fols. irv, Irv, blank.

decoDesc.decoNote:
In the original (s. xii) part of the book major initials are of two kinds, (1) finely drawn, on a pale blue and illuminated background (our Colour Pl. IIa); 
                        and (2) interlace, of less than the first quality, some with columns, acanthus leaves, and biting animal heads, in which the predominant colours are orange, green, blue, yellow, and ochre (our Colour Pl. Ia). 
                        Type 1 is found only in vols. III and IV and type 2 now only in vols. I and II, but tiny parts of type 2 initials are on fol. 149v of vol. III and fol. 58r of vol. IV.

